Jan 2022-Dec 2022 qualification estimates: Following a change to the qualification questions used to derive the highest qualification in 2022, there was a temporary increase in the number of cases where qualification information was not available, which are classified as having "unknown qualifications". This only impacts estimates relating to 2022.

Annual Population Survey (APS) responses are weighted to official population projections. As the current projections are 2018-based they are based on demographic trends that pre-date the COVID-19 pandemic. We are analysing the population totals used in the weighting process and may make adjustments if appropriate. Rates published from the APS remain robust; however, levels and changes in levels should be used with caution. This will particularly affect estimates for country of birth, nationality, ethnicity and disability. This affects all APS periods from April 2019 to March 2020 onwards.
Health and disability variables for APS periods ending Mar 2020, Jun 2020 and Sep 2020 were revised on 2 March 2021. For more details see [http://www.nomisweb.co.uk/articles/1247.aspx].
APS Estimates have not been reweighted to new populations and consequently, will be inconsistent with the population totals used for the Labour Force Survey in the latest periods.
